="1"><mxGeometry x="1601" y="3406" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Person-affecting&lt;br&gt;view&lt;br&gt;[1+5+6+17]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   23 lives-eq/$1k · 15% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up GiveWell top charity (AMF) · 53%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbOztqK5DfZ7uWAtHF2i0u7RZJisagLl5ZoixtJ1JFUHF03%2Fe03JGVbTmTEOH8JFHr0zDOvnNH3k5AuSB6rdzykJ%2BOTszM4Pz%2BHO0FYCopDIMh%2FC3xYpTDNO67XgxUXcfjA6ApW3qw%2FG8w8HxpS8Qw8v6lfnqYIciFlnmSK8RSCCLHG4EJGBA8iRmIN5Y064MGCiBlZkWIW5QlJ5fqHPixylQtaHs8SohQVsxVT0SxkMuB5qli6XIsPIOXV89nO2xttPmRUSJ7OyGJBAyOo7TB8JySIgGxJMwkEPhUqwucFiymgO7Y%2FyzNQEVFAwlC2QFD0IUupBC4MmKBttJUkFEkziecqotYN%2F5BoWRoYjDcQ8CTjUhuyEcB305AiIh4xadCkImlIYp5SSDBIsQPfNjGYPHzTVPXr9DFDo%2FDFBxLnFPjCIGzD5Riwt1QqmOcF5FqNflHSqmFjuHgPkiyoKqBxQ8MV5yHcoBARQdS0GL9MPk5uLu4mlzAvYElTKoiiTlasM4SGTO046xR%2FbGGMlKWk%2FYlIButzGlChtOEJF5gZG79JK2udQrIsZlQ6cFskTsyXKRcJiRvfs34LslH%2FqWmwTMxG7k%2Fw7v0bIzmnitjTTPA5mbOYKSQy59r4UKf3F7cF3lcHrkigOOokglooFMh0JFLVAsmB6vTgYonxm3xZXV5c%2F3H2t68wpzFfYQ7rd0